# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env — build args and non-secret wiring. DO NOT commit (see .gitignore).
#
# Secrets (GitLab tokens, Anthropic API key) live in .catraz/secrets/ —
# one file each, mode 0600, mounted as compose secrets into the relevant
# service. They are NEVER stored here. See docs/design/agentic-workflow/
# 05-packaging/11-compose-rework.md for the rationale.
#
# Non-secret policy (allowed_projects, branch_prefixes, quotas, git hosts) lives
# in .catraz/config/warden.toml — the single source of truth. Edit that file,
# not this one: there are no policy-override env vars here anymore (no git-host,
# no token-mode, no WARDEN_* overrides) — one setting, one source. A host's
# access mode is derived from which of its tokens are present, never stored.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Build ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DEV_UID: auto-derived from id -u by `catraz init` to align bind-mount ownership
# and compose-secret readability. Do NOT hand-edit — a mismatch makes /workspace,
# the warden audit logs, and the mounted secrets unreadable inside the container.
DEV_UID=1000

# Power-user base override — overrides .catraz/config/image/Dockerfile when set.
# Precedence: BASE_IMAGE > BASE_DOCKERFILE(+BASE_CONTEXT) > config/image/Dockerfile.
# Leave unset to use the local Dockerfile (default FROM ubuntu:24.04, editable via init).
# BASE_IMAGE=ghcr.io/you/base:tag           # ready-made image tag (no build step)
# BASE_DOCKERFILE=./docker/Dockerfile.base  # path to an alternative Dockerfile
# BASE_CONTEXT=.                             # build context dir (default: Dockerfile's dir)

# Agent-layer build versions — defaults shown; override to pin Node or the CLI.
NODE_VERSION=22
CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION=latest

# Agent profile (§05.3) — selects assets/agents/<name>/ (adapter + manifest +
# Dockerfile layer). "claude" is the only mitgelieferte profile today; a new
# one is a code change (a new assets/agents/<name>/), never a config value.
AGENT_PROFILE=claude

# ── Wiring (non-secret) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
AUTH_MODE=subscription            # subscription | api_key
# subscription: the active profile's agent.toml `credentials.mode` decides how —
# "persistent" (claude's default): `claude login` once, inside the container;
#   the live home is .catraz/state/<profile>/, so login + refresh survive restarts.
# "sync": host ~/.claude is imported read-only into a tmpfs home via `catraz sync`.
#   Note: tokens refreshed in-session are NOT written back to the host;
#   if auth breaks after a long pause, run `catraz sync` to re-import.
CLAUDE_CREDENTIAL_SOURCE=~/.claude

# Which git hosts the Warden routes to (DNS aliases, git insteadOf rewrites,
# REST base) and the tokens for them are configured entirely in
# .catraz/config/warden.toml ([[git.endpoint]]) and .catraz/secrets/
# (read_tokens/write_tokens) — not here.

# Advanced: remote-control invocation tuning (rarely changed).
# CLAUDE_RC_SPAWN=same-dir
# CLAUDE_RC_DEBUG_FILE=
# CLAUDE_RC_EXTRA_ARGS=

# Change if 3128 is taken; also update http_port in .catraz/config/squid.conf.
# SQUID_PORT=3128
